      "writtenOn": "2020-02-26T18:27:31Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "One thing to consider for multiple tests (assuming they can use the same store) is to use subtests.\n\nInstead of directly calling the common test, you would do:\nfunc TestSQLite(t *testing.T) {\n\n...// setup store\n\nt.Run(\"InsertGet\", func(t *testing.T) {\n   shortcuttest.TestInsertGet(store, t)\n})\nt.Run(\"InsertShortCut\", func(t *testing.T) {\n   shortcuttest.InsertShortCut(store, t)\n})\nt.Run(\"GetNonexistantShortcut_Error\", func(t *testing.T) {\n   shortcuttest.GetNonexistantShortcut_Error(store, t)\n})\n...\n}\n\n\nThat way the setup is only required once, but the tests show up individually and grouped under the SQLite heading.  The CockroachDB would look very similar, except for the different setup code.",
      "revId": "7ccccb79b88f483915b137dca20a501697d683f8",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
